Even if an experimental vaccine seems so far capable of reducing the mortality rate of Ebola, no remedy has yet been sufficiently effective in treating the existing infection.
Even though the administration of a cocktail of antibodies, ZMapp, had initially shown promising signs in the field, formal studies have demonstrated that its ability to reduce deaths did not meet expectations.
In the PALM trial, ZMapp was used as a control, which means that scientists used it as a reference point and compared it to the three other treatments.
The American Gymnastics Federation supports the letter from the United States Olympic Committee and acknowledges the absolute necessity for the Olympic family to promote a safe environment for all of our athletes.
We agree with the statement of the USOC (United States Olympic Committee) that the interests of our athletes and clubs, as well as their sport, could be better served. This could be achieved by moving forward and making significant changes within our organization, rather than revoking accreditation.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that could shed light on how the abuse of the magnitude courageously described by Larry Nassar's survivors could have gone unnoticed for so long and is committed to making any necessary and appropriate changes.
USA Gymnastics and the USOC have the same goal: to make gymnastics, as well as other sports, as safe as possible so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a safe, positive, and empowering environment.
