They observed that the Sun operates according to the same basic principles as other stars. The activity of all the stars in the system is determined by their brightness, their rotation, and nothing else.
Brightness and rotation are used together to determine the Rossby number of a star, which is related to the plasma flow.
Regarding magnetic inversions, the smaller the Rossby number, the less active the star is.
