The 802.11n standard operates on both the 2.4 GHz and 5.0 GHz frequencies.
This will allow backward compatibility with 802.11a, b, and g iterations, provided that the station has two radios.
The speeds of the Wi-Fi standard 802.11n are significantly faster than those of its predecessors, with a maximum theoretical speed of 600 Mbit/s.
